:: Start {"position":"700,50","size":"200,100"}
Oh, hey! Sorry -- just give me one second. I'm right in the middle of something and I just need to finish this thought real quick...

[photo: start]

[[Wait patiently.->Introduction]]
[[I'm actually in a bit of a hurry.->In a Hurry Intro]]


:: Introduction {"position":"450,300","size":"200,100"}
Hey, sorry about that. My name's Josh. I'm a programmer, and sometimes I just need to get the thought out of my head before it's gone forever. So sorry it took me a second.

But you have my full attention now. Welcome to my portfolio site!

So here's the thing -- there are so many developers out there who just have a pretty static page with the basic information about who they are. It shows you that they can build a website. But it doesn't show you their creativity, their passion, and you don't really get to know them at all through their site.

I wanted more than a website. I wanted an experience. I wanted to show what I'm passionate about and kind of introduce myself to anybody who's made it here looking for information on me. So I'll be your guide to, well... me, if you will.

What do you want to know?

[photo: introduction]

