:: About Origin {"position":"50,1350","size":"200,100"}
How'd I get into this? Well... my grandpa is a doctor, and my dad was an aircraft mechanic.

They both loved working with their hands, and they both showed me the value of solving problems. That's where my love for this type of work really started -- and I always was naturally very good with technology.

I loved learning and I loved school, but I couldn't afford more than community college, and I could never figure out how to get enough scholarships to get through a four-year computer science program.

So after a few years working the best jobs I could -- ones that usually paid around minimum wage -- I decided I was sick and tired of lifting heavy things more than using my mind.

Luckily, I found an opportunity at a boot camp and I took it. For six months I was a sponge, absorbing everything I could about software, pulling on knowledge from the few college classes I had taken, all while working a full-time job.

By the end, I was able to land a job working primarily in the .NET stack. What was intended to be an internship turned into a short apprenticeship, and next thing you know I had my first official job as a full-time full-stack software engineer. That was in early 2022.

[photo: about_origin]

[[Give me your elevator pitch.->Elevator Pitch]]
[[What are your hopes and dreams?->Hopes and Dreams]]
[[Tell me about your career after that.->Experience Intro]]
[[Take me to "The Core" navigation.->The Core]]


:: Hopes and Dreams {"position":"50,1600","size":"200,100"}
Hopes and dreams? Really, I just want to have a job that provides for my wife Ruthie and I and allows me to keep my house in order and provide for my family as a whole.

I love doing meaningful work that impacts people's lives and makes them better. As long as I'm doing that and helping people become better and helping our society become better, I will be happy. I will feel satisfied in the work I do.

I have dabbled in game development because I really enjoy the interaction games can have with people and the uplifting experience they can provide. If the opportunity ever presents itself, I would love to get into the gaming industry. But if it never happens, it's not the end of the world.

Some of the areas that really excite me are space exploration, electric vehicles, solar energy -- basically anything that pushes us closer to a high-tech, sci-fi future. You can tell by the style of this website that I really enjoy that kind of thing.

I want to push our society to a cooler, more high-tech future. And I feel like all of these things -- solar, EVs, space -- are on the horizon, getting closer and closer to our everyday lives. Which I love.

[[What are your career goals specifically?->Career Goals]]
[[How'd you get into software?->About Origin]]
[[Show me some projects you've built.->Projects Intro]]
[[Take me to "The Core" navigation.->The Core]]


:: Faith {"position":"50,1850","size":"200,100"}
My faith is really important to me. It's not a side note -- it's pretty central to how I operate.

I'm a Christian. I attend church regularly and I serve there in multiple capacities. Right now I'm serving as a production producer -- I orchestrate between sound, lighting, slides, cameras. I'm kind of the orchestrator of all of that, if you will.

I have a firm belief that the systems around us -- plants, ecosystems, the balance of nature -- were designed in a very meticulous and intentional way. A lot of what I do, especially in gardening, is just figuring out what that design is and how to work with it.

My faith influences how I treat people, how I approach my work, and honestly, how I think about technology too. I feel like the sun was put there intentionally so that we could use it to fuel our lives. Solar panels, renewable energy -- those things just make sense to me on a deeper level.

It's who I am. And I'm not shy about it.

[photo: faith]

