:: Hobbies Garden {"position":"200,1100","size":"200,100"}
I could talk about gardening for days. Okay so this one is hard to explain without sounding a little intense, but -- I'm building an orchard.

Not like, casually. I mean planning it out, thinking about regenerative systems, composting, perennial planting, pollinators, soil health. I've got Flavorfest strawberries going, I'm experimenting with mushroom log cultivation -- shiitake, lion's mane, oysters -- and I'm slowly working toward permaculture-style growing methods.

I have a firm belief that the plants and the ecosystem around us were designed in a very meticulous and intentional way. A lot of gardening is just figuring out what that way is. How to work with the design and intention of this world, of the ecosystem, of the plants that grow and the creatures that live here.

The more you get into it, the more beautiful the balance is. The harmony, the synergy -- it's just, in my opinion, not from random chance. Everything works together in a very intentional way and it's very soothing.

And it's a huge break from technology. I love technology, and there's a lot of really cool things that interest me. But gardening is completely different -- completely detached from manufactured systems. You're working with systems that have been around since the creation of life on this earth.

[photo: hobbies_garden]

[[Tell me about the 3D printing.->Hobbies Maker]]
[[Tell me about the gaming.->Hobbies Gaming]]
