:: Hobbies Maker {"position":"400,1100","size":"200,100"}
I like to do 3D printing. I have an Ender S1+ and I've absolutely gone down the rabbit hole with it.

I do a lot of actual printing, tuning of the printer, working with the slicer, all different kinds of stuff like that. It's just a really enjoyable hobby. I know how to use CAD software, but I still have a lot to learn -- I'm definitely not a professional CAD modeler yet. But I'm working towards it, one project at a time.

The biggest thing is I don't like trinkets. I like functional things. So I usually use my printer for practical stuff -- custom mounts, solutions for things that don't have off-the-shelf answers. There's a real satisfaction in looking at a problem and building the answer instead of buying it.

Beyond that, I love home improvement and workshop projects. It overlaps heavily with coding, honestly. It's all just problem-solving in different materials.

[photo: hobbies_maker]

