:: Software Career {"position":"550,1100","size":"200,100"}
I've been in software since late 2021. I started right after my boot camp, making small sites for e-commerce companies and other freelance gigs I could find.

After that, I found an opportunity at a company called Sharp Hue. I started there as an apprentice and worked my way up to full-stack software developer, then software developer II.

Each step brought more ownership, more complex assignments, and more systems that actually matter.

At Sharp Hue, I've mainly worked with C#, ASP.NET MVC, JavaScript, jQuery, Knockout.js, Dynamics 365 CRM, Azure, Entity Framework, Blob Storage, and Azure Functions -- across a large range of enterprise projects.

My freelance work can be just about anything. Anyone who needs software and reaches out to me, we work out a deal and I get it done. It's been mostly different JavaScript frontend frameworks so far.

