:: Volunteer Experience {"position":"550,1350","size":"200,100"}
Have I volunteered? Absolutely. I'm very passionate about serving my community and serving my church. My faith is really important to me, and so that's my go-to when I talk about volunteering -- I've definitely put the most hours into my local church.

When I was in high school, I operated the soundboard for my youth group. I've done data entry for churches. I've really helped out in a lot of different aspects.

Currently, for the past few years now, I've been serving in a production producer capacity. So I orchestrate between the different teams on production at my church -- I coordinate between sound, lighting, slides, cameras. I'm kind of the orchestrator of all of that, if you will.

And I can do just about any of it to a certain capacity, at least. I help troubleshoot issues, try and debug different things -- just like I would in my normal software job, but applied in a little bit more of a leadership role.

I've also volunteered here and there at smaller things. And my church is also very good about helping out our community.

