:: Tech Intro {"position":"1300,850","size":"200,100"}
So my main tech stack is .NET, ASP.NET, C#. That whole ecosystem -- that's what I have almost three years of professional experience in. And that is what I'm by far the most familiar with, because I work with it 40 hours every week.

I work a little bit with PHP now and then, but it's a lot less than my .NET API back-end work.

I'm really familiar with React -- it's what this site was built with. The first stack I learned was the MERN stack. I also obviously know the basics: HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript. I use a lot of jQuery and I'm very familiar with it.

But if you want the whole background, I can take you there. This section is more about what stacks I'd say right off the bat that I'm proficient in.

