:: Databases {"position":"1450,1100","size":"200,100"}
What type of databases have I interacted with? Good question.

With the MERN stack, it was MongoDB -- a document database. And then for the majority of my time working in .NET, it's been mostly Microsoft databases. So just your standard SQL databases. I run queries against them, I've worked with them quite a lot.

I think I kind of prefer standard SQL databases, because they have a little bit more type safety, which is especially useful in the .NET environment.

I've also used Postgres with some Node back-ends. But I think the type safety that comes with .NET and C# really lends itself to standard SQL databases, whereas JavaScript being kind of a little more free-form works better with JSON or document databases like Mongo.

[photo: databases]

