:: Least Favorite Tech {"position":"1350,1600","size":"200,100"}
Honestly? Java. It was one of the first languages I learned, but it's just so verbose. I've built projects using Spring Boot, but I was never able to make the code feel clean and simple.

It's just not for me. There are several successors to C++ -- I'll go with just about any of the others, including my language of choice: C#.

